# How do you think AI (artificial intelligence) will affect people's work?
I think artificial intelligence will have a big impact on people’s work. On the one hand, it can automate repetitive tasks and make the workflow more efficient, allowing employees to focus on more important and creative work. On the other hand, it may replace some jobs, especially entry-level ones. Overall, I believe AI will change the way we work, and people will need to be flexible and continuously learn new skills to stay relevant in the job market.

# What would you say are the important factors to consider when choosing a career?
In my view, the most vital factor is personal fulfillment, as individuals are far more likely to remain driven if they are passionate about their daily tasks. That said, remuneration cannot be overlooked; a competitive salary is essential for maintaining a comfortable standard of living. Lastly, I believe work-life balance is crucial to ensure that professional responsibilities do not come at the expense of one's physical or mental health. Ultimately, a successful career is one that harmonizes professional ambition with personal lifestyle needs.

# Technology will make some people lose their jobs. How do you think this problem should be handled?
I think this problem should be handled through a combination of reskilling and government support. As technology replaces certain jobs, workers need to learn new skills so they can move into roles that are less likely to be automated. At the same time, governments should provide training programs and financial assistance to help people during this transition. In addition, individuals need to be adaptable and willing to keep learning. Overall, with the right support and mindset, the negative impact of technology on employment can be reduced.

Is it common in your country for people to move to other cities because of work?
Yes, it’s quite common in my country, especially among young people. Many of them move to big cities like Ho Chi Minh City or Hanoi in search of better job opportunities and higher salaries. Large cities tend to offer more career options, particularly in fields like business, technology, and services. Although this can improve their quality of life, it can also lead to challenges such as high living costs and homesickness.
